title: For Sale:  KEL-TEC p-11
postcontent:
The P-11 is a semi-automatic, locked-breech, DAO, pistol, chambered for the 9mm Luger cartridge. Ten round and optional twelve round magazines available. The Kel- Tec P-11 is compact and lightweight, thanks to its locked breech. Its ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-11 is especially well suited for plain-clothes police officers, security personnel, or as a secondary weapon for military service members. 

The P-11 has six main component groups: barrel, slide, frame, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 Ordnance steel heat treated to 47 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer and operates in Double Action Only. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. The functioning of the mechanism surpasses all applicable SAAMI safety standards. The grip is made of the ultra high impact polymer DuPont ST-8018. The grip also forms the magazine well and the trigger guard. Normally supplied with a 10-round double column all steel magazine.

1st Stop FireArms REDACTED

title: For Sale:  1921 DWM Luger
postcontent:
This is a rare DWM Luger manufactured in 1921.  This Luger was originally issued to the Stuttgart V Corps, and bears that marking on the front strap as well as the correct Police proofs.  There is a chip missing from the left grip from the safety (very common with these).  All serial numbers are matching, and the springs are properly colored from the heat treat.  The magazine plug is broken and is the later plastic type.  It is not matched to the pistol.

Also included is a Waffenamt marked holster.  It is marked 1941 and comes complete with the multi-purpose tool.  

This pistol is in roughly 80% shape, and is perfect for the beginning collector with a desire to posses a good example of a Weimar Republic 9mm.

title: For Sale:  Custom Knife - Rainbow Damascus Blade, Premium White Mother of Perl Scales with Diamond Tipped Thumb Stud and Screws
postcontent:
This is an amazing custom diamond studded Damascus liner ultimate gentleman’s folder knife is a collaboration by unknown artists. It is not signed, but the knife may be a Don Hansen or a Jeff Hall creation before the diamond screws were added. I've never seen another like it. What makes this absolutely unique knife an amazing piece are the 6 diamond headed gold screws and gold diamond thumb stud; these were meticulously handmade and added by a jeweler/knife dealer as a prototype example for customizing knives and, unfortunately I acquired it quite a number of years ago at a knife show and I cannot remember the jeweler/dealer’s name. The blade is Damascus stainless anodized with dark purplish-maroon hues. The bolsters are highly blued Damascus. The scales are premium mother-of-pearl with gold pins. The blade is 3.6” and the knife is 8.5” overall. It is a liner lock. The liner and back strap are fully file worked and the spacer is anodized blue. The materials alone are worth the price. Additional detailed photos can be seen at

title: For Sale:  Sig 556 xi
postcontent:
Like new in box Sig 556 xi. This rifle only has approximately 400 rounds through it. It shoots great and I was getting 1.5 moa groups at 100 yards with 75gr hornady match ammo.  It is a ton of fun. The 556 is described as a hybrid of the Ar-15 and AK platform. The xi is the modular variant which is multi caliber convertible with purchase of a different caliber upper. This rifle has a 3-position adjustable gas piston operating system with a rotating locking AK style bolt. The fore end is on a quick release and disassembly of the firearm is very similar to an Ar-15 style platform. Everything on it is ambi (charging handle, safety, mag release, bolt catch). It comes with a folding side stock from the factory, which I have swapped for a DDLS adapter with a magpul CTR stock ($175 mod). Both stocks will come with the gun. It also comes with 6 magazines, 5 of which are P-mags. The original iron sights, a soft case, a set of canted iron sights and a single point harness are included. Also have original box.

For more information view Sig’s website at the link below.

http://www.sigsauer.com/CatalogProductDetails/sig556xi-standard.aspx

title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith S&W Colt 1911 Stainless Restoration Service
postcontent:
Stainless Refinish Service for S&W, Colt, Kimber, others.

We specialize in S&W Gen 2 and 3 stainless pistols and accurately match the factory media blasted finish.  We can also refinish Colt and other stainless firearm parts.

The price is to refinish one pistol slide which has been detailed stripped (completely disassembled) and ready for the refinishing.  The price does not include hand working for a brushed finish (as on S&W 639, 645 and others) or to eliminate cuts, scratches, agency markings or gouges.  Email and send photos for quote. Our price for a pistol frame/slide/barrel combination is $85 and includes small parts such as slide release, safety levers and other associated small stainless (only) parts.

We do not offer gunsmith or dis-assembly services, though we are familiar with Smith Gen 2 and 3 pistols and may consider a complete rebuild depending upon the model (Additional cost.  Minimum $65 for dis - re - assemble).  Support your local gunsmith (and tell them of our service please) and ask for their assistance if you are unable to detail strip your pistol.  See the many "YouTube" videos if you're a "Do-It-Yourself" person and want to save money.

Due to the low volume for our service, we only schedule one run per month.  Next run is on or about June 1.

Slides and non-FFL parts may be shipped direct.  Frames and receivers must be shipped to our FFL.

Return shipping is actual USPS postage.  Add $10 FFL handling fee when shipping needs to be done through my FFL (frames and such).  Add for insurance over the standard USPS $50.00.

We would like to work with and offer an FFL/Gunsmith discount.

The PMR-30 is a light weight, full size pistol chambered for Newthe flat-shooting .22Magnum cartridge (.22WMR). The PMR-30 operates on a unique hybrid blowback/locked-breech system. This operation system allows for the use of a wide variety of ammunition as it seamlessly adjusts between locked breech and blowback operation, depending on the pressure of the cartridge. It uses a double stack magazine of a new design that holds 30 rounds and fits completely in the grip of the pistol. The trigger is a crisp single action with an over-travel stop. Slide and barrel are 4140 steel, frame is 7075 aluminum. Grip, slide cover, trigger, mag release, and safety levers are glass reinforced Nylon (Zytel), much like other Kel-Tec Pistols. Other features include: dual opposing extractors for reliability, heel magazine release to aid in magazine retention, dovetailed aluminum front sight, Picatinny accessory rail under the barrel, Urethane recoil buffer, captive coaxial recoil springs. PMR30 disassembles for cleaning by removal of a single pin.

title: For Sale:  SIG SAUER P320
postcontent:
Introducing the P320, a polymer-framed service pistol designed from the ground up with the input of law enforcement officers. The result is the most operator-safety focused striker duty pistol on the market today. 

Taking into account the concerns of military and police training officers, the P320 provides an enhanced level of safety not found on most modern service pistols. Unlike its competitors, the P320 does not require the operator to pull the trigger nor use a special tool to take-down the firearm for cleaning or routine maintenance. 

Featuring a modular grip frame and removable fire control assembly pioneered by SIG SAUER, the P320 is customizable to any hand size or duty requirement. The P320 can quickly be converted from a Full-size to a Carry pistol. Slide and barrel conversions allow the P320 to change between calibers and barrel lengths as well. The P320 will be immediately available in 9mm, .40S&W and .357SIG, with .45ACP coming later in 2014. 

With a partially pretensioned striker, the P320 has a short, crisp trigger pull with a quick, pronounced reset right out-of-the-box. The P320 comes in two trigger variants: a standard trigger and a tabbed safety trigger for specific law enforcement clients. Featuring the SIG SAUER internal safety system, the P320 has no external safety or decocking lever to snag or hang up on the draw. A frame-mounted thumb safety version will be available for law enforcement needs. SIGLITE® night sights come standard, and the reversible magazine release makes the P320 completely ambidextrous. 

Whatever the requirement, patrol duty, competition, time at the shooting range, or concealed carry, the P320 brings SIG SAUER legendary reliability, durability, and quality to the polymer-framed, striker-fired duty pistol

1st Stop Firearms
